  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Inception of the Institute for Forensic Psychiatry Sokolac</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">Consequences of the war in the former Yugoslavia are felt in BiH until today. A significant part of the population suffers from mental health problems. In line with the European Convention on Human Rights, people with mental disorders committing crimes have the right to adequate treatment in custody. SDC and SECO therefore support the opening of the first Institute for Forensic Psychiatry in BiH, from whose services up to 200 convicts with mental disorders from across BiH will benefit.</narrative>
  </description>
